# ALPE Games catalog — multi-agent rules

Reference: `WORKFLOW.md` at the repo root.

## Branch ownership

- Never push to `main` directly. Create a branch (`feat/<short>`, `fix/<short>`, or `agent/<issue>-<slug>`).
- One branch has one owner at a time.
- Registry additions go on a dedicated branch named after the game slug, e.g. `registry/<slug>`.

## Scope discipline

- Every code change references a GitHub issue.
- Catalog UI changes and registry entries should be separate PRs whenever possible.
- Do not redesign the site during an active game cycle. If a redesign is needed, open a tracking issue and defer.

## Registry edits

- `data/games.registry.json` is the contract between game repos and the site. Run `npm run validate:registry` after any change.
- New games must have `embed.url` of the form `https://gamejam.alpegames.cl/games/{slug}/` (unless `embed.type` is `external`).
- HEAD-check the play URL before merging the registry entry.

## Reviewer mode

- When asked to review a PR or registry change, do not push commits unless explicitly requested.
- For a registry PR, confirm: slug uniqueness, URL pattern, postmortem link, and ship checklist.

## PR hygiene

- Keep PRs small. Catalog changes should not bundle multiple games.
- Do not touch `.github/workflows/*.yml` or `infra/` unless the task is explicitly CI or VPS work.
